Today's **Contest Results** are in! 🎉🫡

# Introducing EdgeMaxxing v4.0

## **__Big update time :coolguy: __**
We're proud to introduce v4.0 of our Subnet, featuring a number of major upgrades & improvements. Read on for more details:
- Code for nerds here: https://github.com/womboai/edge-maxxing/pull/57
- The purpose of these changes is to improve contest performance, VTRUST stability, and take EdgeMaxxing to the next level 

## **__Instructions__**
- **__Validators__**: Please update to the latest version
- **__Miners__**: You're good, keep EdgeMaxxing 💪 

## **__Changelog:__**
- All validators will now test all miners using the same set of inputs, which are revealed to validators at benchmarking time, thus ensuring consistent results for miners across different validators
- To ensure optimizations don't hurt quality, we have implemented a minimum similarity threshold, along with similarities at the lower end of the range getting far lower scores
- New incentive distribution system that gives more rewards relative to the score improvement, rather than to only a single winner or a leaderboard of winners. More details: https://github.com/womboai/edge-maxxing/blob/inputs-api/validator/weight_setting/winner_selection.py#L20)
- Better deduplication handling which gives **__0 incentive to copiers__** 
- Greatly improved benchmarking time, due to many different optimizations relating to the set of inputs, caching and duplicate detection
 - All submissions and now benchmarked daily to keep rewards moving and ensure no one continues being a winner simply by getting lucky
- HUGE amount of bugfixes, including some related to wandb and multiple validation APIs
- Updated miner submission spec
- Scores are now included in wandb (more data to be added soon™️)
- Better blacklist handling and blacklisting keys who have only copied other models to earn emission without optimizing

## **__LINKS:__**
- Leaderboard: https://huggingface.co/spaces/wombo/edge-maxxing-leaderboard
- Validator States: https://huggingface.co/spaces/wombo/edge-maxxing-validator-states
- Weights: https://huggingface.co/spaces/wombo/edge-maxxing-weights
- Github: https://github.com/womboai/edge-maxxing

## **__Wrapping up:__**
We've come quite far since launching EdgeMaxxing and have produced a substantially optimized version of Stable Diffusion thanks to the contributions of miners in this Subnet. But we're just getting started - stay tuned for more updates, and our new compeition starting soon ❤️ 

**EdgeMaxxing Forever :coolguy: :coolguy: :coolguy: :coolguy:**

Hello @deleted-role! Here is an update of the state of things along with some new pushes
Previously seen issues:
- Validators not finishing benchmarking
   - Reason: state management bugs between validator and benchmarking API, which have now been fixed

- Dashboards not working
   - Reason 1: The 4.0.0 update had changed wandb run signatures format, along with some of how the data is structured. The dashboards have now been updated to fix that
   - Reason 2: the latest version of the `gradio` package, which huggingface uses, appears to have a broken dependency requirement, that is out of our control.

Overall state:
- Most validators except 68 and 39 could not set proper weights or finish benchmarking
- Validators 68 and 39 had both finished and set weights, but due to other validators having different weights, but since no other validators have set (new) weights, vtrust remains at 0 and thus all incentives are still 0

- These issues will go away with the new update after validators run it for long enough that they set new weights

New/current version: 4.1.1
- Changes:
   - Similarity threshold is even more strict than before, using the lowest similarity score rather than the average to test the threshold
   - Change duplicate detection to also compare the generation time difference, to avoid false positives
   - Miner benchmarking script now tests similarity against the baseline
   - Optimize benchmark cancellation when benchmarks are invalidated
- Fixes:
   - Resolve some validator OOM issues preventing proper benchmarking
   - Fix validator API state bugs

We will continue to resolve issues as swiftly as possible and make sure that this contest goes well before the end of the week, thank you all for your patience and support!

hey miners! we've released a new update that requires you to update and resubmit your models. this update switches the package manager from `pip` to `uv`, allowing for significantly faster benchmarking time.

3. add your dependencies to the `pyproject.toml` file and ensure the version is set to `6`
4. relock the `uv.lock` file with `uv lock`
5. resubmit

# The new FLUX Schnell Contest will be launching today at 4:00 PM, 11/25/2024 4:00 PM from now!

**What is FLUX Schnell**
FLUX Schnell is an advanced image model that surpasses SDXL in generating high quality images. While it delivers exceptional results, it also comes with higher computational demands. The baseline model requires the full 24GB of VRAM from an NVIDIA RTX 4090 GPU, necessitating the unloading of components after use to manage resources effectively.

**Contest Goals:**
1. **Primary Objective:** Improve the model’s VRAM efficiency to enable pre-loading. This will allow FLUX Schnell to run on devices with lower VRAM capacities and enhance overall performance.
2. **Secondary Objective:** Reduce image generation times without compromising quality, making the model more efficient and user-friendly.

**Submissions will be evaluated primarily on how effectively they reduce VRAM usage while maintaining similarity to the original model’s outputs, with a bonus for lowering generation times.**

We have just pushed a series of updates, most are general improvements but along them is changing the metric handling to punish having generation time that's too much lower than the baseline(or in general having too low of any metric), the actual weight of the generation time metric has also been bumped to encourage keeping a good balance of VRAM and speed

Miners who have been in the subnet for a long time have seen many updates in favor of Robert, although I don't claim there is anything shady going on. We can only assume he is a child of god. I've also come to fully appreciate some of his optimizations.

https://github.com/womboai/edge-maxxing/pull/98/commits/1ff94b5f237fd507121beef5f11500fc9fc5b57b
what kind of updates?

I'll just name a few:
- I was the winner of this subnet before Robert, the winner's reward was only 0.5 incentive during that time, and it was immediately increased to 0.65 and then 0.9 after Robert took the lead.
- Robert once 1:1 copied my solution, which led to his coldkey being blacklisted, but he was later pardoned. I've never seen any other coldkeys being pardoned (I could be wrong).
- There was a time when the incentive mechanism of the subnet was completely broken. Robert was the winner by accident at that time (he had a lot of hotkeys). There was no fix for almost a week, Robert got the entire reward during that time. Another day a cheater exploited internet access to win against Robert, the fix was immediately released within a few hours, saving him from any damage.

gen time is currently very inconsistent across machines due to a heavier reliance on CPU than there should be, we're tweaking the optimization parameters to push away from the kind of optimizations that rely heavily on the CPU in any capacity
we'll be pushing an update soon(before EOW) which removes the bias towards older submissions while still effectively not rewarding copies

we've given prior notice to you, Robert and other miners prior to changes to increase everyone's chances at better competing, no one has been given special treatment
(this is what we've been doing for a while, https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1241046233800507482/1299158505881604196)

addressing each point separately here:
- that was just bad timing, the percentage was low initially to avoid vtrust unstability when the winner selection was less stable, as things got more stable and more complaints were sent(including by you, https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1241046233800507482/1299171163771109477) the percentage got higher
  - unstability has been the main motivator for a lot of changes in this subnet, including the more conservative distribution used recently which happens to favor older models
- a few keys have been removed from the blacklist, not just Robert's. we remove people from the blacklist if they message us proving they have made actual optimization contributions before or that they have plans to do so, which Robert did
- ~~what was broken with the mechanism at the time? I don't recall what was broken since it has been a while~~ (nevermind I assume it was the tier handling being relative to the scores rather than an absolute point, we just weren't sure how to deal with that and were discussing internally the best steps to move forward, that's kind of what we're *still* dealing with), the exploit however was quickly patched as it would have completely undermined the efforts of the subnet

Robert has been winning mostly because he monitors the subnet code pushes closely and submits models which cover any changes we might make(for example submitting both a quantized and a CPU offloaded model, the latter of which won initially, and as we changed the contest to favor speed, the quantized version won)

our next steps to push this contest forward will be as follows:
- changing the distribution to not favor old models while still preventing copies
- increasing the similarity requirement back up
- giving more weight to the CPU memory and speed metrics to incentivize making the model as fast as possible

Hello @deleted-role!
We have now updated the baseline for the Flux model using one of @Roberτ's quantized models, in an effort to push the contest towards speed and reducing the amount of CPU offloading and other CPU reliant work that submissions currently do, the submission spec has been updated to `8`, please update your submission along with the version and models in `pyproject.toml` accordingly!

We have also updated the huggingface models format, to allow more control over their downloading:
```toml
[[tool.edge-maxxing.models]]
repository = "black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell"
revision = "741f7c3ce8b383c54771c7003378a50191e9efe9"

# optionally
include = [...]
exclude = [...]
```
was mainly an effort to push towards quantization(thus less RAM usage) and to reduce CPU specific work
the weights no longer specify VRAM or RAM, it's just generation speed as the metric now
The only framework which works with a 'runtime' environment is TorchAO.
And you all may see that torchao int8 are being used every where.

the similarity is now based on the new quantized baseline, which yes uses a quantized transformer with torchao int8
the contest is now all about speed, you don't need to worry about quantizing it to a smaller size, just making it faster :)

Hello @deleted-role!

We are experimenting with some updates to the weight distribution system, our goals are as follows:
- Reward everyone for their optimization efforts
- Still give top optimizers more incentive
- Give copiers no incentive

We have pushed one update to progress our goal, which rewards miners more closely based on their score rather than just taking the top spot, and we have started blacklisting more copiers to ensure all weight goes to honest miners actually pushing the subnet forward

With that, we are closer to achieving #1 and #2. While our blacklist fills the role of #3, we are working on an internal automation system to allow it to happen autonomously and accurately, with the ability for manual intervention and disputes on false positives.

We hope to achieve all 3 goals before the end of the week, and we are well on our way to do so. Thank you as always for your continuous participation, and happy EdgeMaxxing!

hey @deleted-role!

Thanks for all the feedback on the duplicate submission detection. A few changes we've made since the last announcement:
- the duplicate submission list (https://edge-inputs.api.wombo.ai/duplicate_submissions) now acts as a whitelist. this means that submissions need to be evaluated first **before** they're benchmarked, which should prevent model copiers from ever receiving incentive in the first place.
- Submissions on this list are now tied to a particular revision. This means that if you update your submission, it'll be reevaluated before being benchmarked.

### Why is registration closed?
We've closed registration due to an overwhelming amount of fake submissions causing most legitimate miners to lose many of their keys. to prevent this from happening again, we'll open registration once we've addressed all this issues with the current cheat detection system

### What's up with the weights?
We've had some recent issues with the weights not aligning with contest results. We'll look into these issues this week, starting with disabling commit reveal temporarily to potentially mitigate the issue while we investigate the root cause

I'll also be going through the reports in https://discord.com/channels/799672011265015819/1327411373193433139 this week, mainly addressing the issues with false-positives

Happy EdgeMaxxing 🫡
